<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Cylinder Head And Valves -
        Cylinder Head Assembly - Valve Lever
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="6">
        <title>Valve Lever</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Disassembly</title>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1918.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Disassemble the Valve Lever</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Lever Clip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Lever Post</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Chrome Ball</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Lever</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>BE SURE to keep all items of each rocker lever together for installation in their original
                        locations.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully remove the valve lever clip that secures the valve lever, valve lever post,
                    and the 10 mm (3/8 in) chrome ball.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the chrome ball from the cup on the valve lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Separate the valve lever from valve lever post.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Cleaning</title>
            <para>Clean all parts with a suitable solvent and dry parts using filtered compressed air.</para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Inspection</title>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Valve Lever Component Relationship</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining Clip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Lever Post</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Chrome Ball</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Lever</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Lever Assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the valve stem ends and corresponding valve lever pads for pitting or scuffing.
                    Inspect the chrome ball and ball socket in valve lever for scuffing. Replace the levers as required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the valve lever post ball socket for excessive wear. Inspect the bolts for
                    thread damage. Replace worn components as required.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Assembly</title>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2014A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Lubricating the Chrome Ball</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the chrome ball on the valve lever cup. Lubricate the chrome ball with clean
                    engine oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2014B.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Installing the Valve Lever Post</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the valve lever post on the chrome ball.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2014C.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Installing the Retaining Clip</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, install the retaining clip correctly. Failure to do so could result in
                        valve lever assembly coming apart in the running engine.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Snap the retaining clip over the valve lever post groove.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1790.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Valve Lever Retaining Clip Position</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining Clip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Lever</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Lever Post</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Pivot Ball</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
